<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════
     5. KEY THINGS TO KNOW (Tabs)
═══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="cd-tabs">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Key Things to Know</h2>
    <div class="cd-tabs__wrap">
      <div class="cd-tabs__nav">
        <button class="tab-btn active" data-tab="1">AWS Solutions<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="2">Azure & GCP<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="3">Cloud Migration<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="4">DevOps & Automation<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
        <button class="tab-btn" data-tab="5">Cost Optimization<i class="fas fa-chevron-right tab-arrow"></i></button>
      </div>
      <div class="cd-tabs__content">
        <div class="tab-panel active" data-panel="1">
          <p>Amazon Web Services remains the world's leading cloud platform, with the broadest service catalog and the largest ecosystem of partners and tooling. The Demski Group leverages EC2, Lambda, ECS, RDS, S3, CloudFront, and dozens of other AWS services to build architectures that are secure, scalable, and cost-optimized.</p><p>Whether you need a simple S3-hosted static site or a complex multi-region microservices platform, our AWS-certified engineers design and implement solutions that match your exact requirements — and help you avoid the most common (and expensive) cloud architecture mistakes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="2">
          <p>Microsoft Azure is the preferred cloud for organizations deeply invested in the Microsoft ecosystem, offering tight integration with Active Directory, Office 365, and on-premise Windows Server environments. Google Cloud Platform excels in data analytics, machine learning, and Kubernetes workloads, backed by Google's global network infrastructure.</p><p>The Demski Group has certified engineers across all three major platforms and can help you evaluate the right choice — or design a multi-cloud strategy that avoids vendor lock-in while taking advantage of each platform's unique strengths.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="3">
          <p>Migrating to the cloud is a significant undertaking that requires careful planning to avoid disruption. The Demski Group follows a structured migration methodology: discover and assess your current environment, map dependencies, select the right migration strategy (lift-and-shift, re-platform, or re-architect), and execute with a detailed cutover plan.</p><p>Our post-migration validation process verifies that every workload performs correctly in its new environment before you decommission on-premise resources, giving you confidence that the transition was truly seamless.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="4">
          <p>Modern software delivery demands automation at every stage. The Demski Group builds CI/CD pipelines using GitHub Actions, Jenkins, or GitLab CI that automatically test, build, and deploy your application on every commit — eliminating manual deployments and the human errors that come with them.</p><p>We pair automated pipelines with infrastructure-as-code using Terraform or Pulumi, ensuring your entire cloud environment is version-controlled, reproducible, and auditable, making disaster recovery and environment replication straightforward operations.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="5">
          <p>Cloud costs can spiral out of control without active governance. The Demski Group conducts thorough cost analysis using AWS Cost Explorer, Azure Cost Management, or GCP Billing to identify over-provisioned resources, idle instances, and opportunities to shift to reserved or spot pricing models.</p><p>We implement tagging policies, budget alerts, and rightsizing recommendations that give your finance and engineering teams the visibility they need to keep cloud spending predictable and aligned with the business value each workload delivers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

