    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="true">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          Which cloud platform is right for my business?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a" style="display:block;">It depends on your existing technology stack, compliance requirements, and long-term roadmap. AWS offers the broadest service catalog; Azure integrates seamlessly with Microsoft tools; GCP excels in data and ML workloads. We help you evaluate the options and make the right choice for your specific situation.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          How disruptive is a cloud migration?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">With proper planning, migrations can be nearly invisible to end users. We use phased cutover strategies, blue-green deployments, and extensive pre-migration testing to keep your services running throughout the transition.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          How do you control cloud costs?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">We implement resource tagging, budget alerts, auto-scaling policies, and regular rightsizing reviews. We also advise on reserved instance and savings plan purchases that can reduce your compute bill by 30–60% for predictable workloads.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          What is infrastructure as code and why does it matter?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">Infrastructure as code means your entire cloud environment — networks, servers, databases, and all — is defined in version-controlled configuration files rather than clicked together manually in a console. This makes your infrastructure reproducible, auditable, and dramatically easier to recover from failure.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <i class="fas fa-minus icon-open"></i>
          <i class="fas fa-plus icon-closed"></i>
          Can you help with cloud security and compliance?
        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">Absolutely. We implement IAM best practices, VPC network segmentation, encryption at rest and in transit, WAF rules, and compliance controls. We've helped clients achieve SOC 2 Type II, HIPAA, and GDPR compliance on AWS, Azure, and GCP.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

